description:
In space, no one can hear you scream . . . or belch, or swear, or cry like a little girl when you're about to be taken down by merciless interstellar bounty hunters who want that mysterious idol you swiped from that hot chick who inexplicably gave you the tip of a lifetime (if you know what I mean) when you showed up at the wrong hotel room with the pizza delivery. This assumes that "you" are ne'er-do-well big-talker Quinn and explains-sort of-how "you" hooked up (not like that!) with a big badass of a former galactic cop (and current mama's boy) by the name of Krunk, who is not your partner and not your buddy, got it? Oh, and by the way, the hot chick is hotter than ever (in the bad way) and she wants that idol back, and this time she's probably going to give you a different kind of gratuity, like with a laser ax or a plasma grenade or something. Try talking your way out of that one, spacehole!

Created by Zach Howard (Shaun of the Dead) and Sean Murphy (Scarecrow: Year One; Off Road), with screenwriter Reed Buccholz, Outer Orbit is outrageous, rude, hilarious space fantasy that takes the time-honored traditions of this beloved genre and leaves them face-down in a filthy alley in a pool of their own sick.

In this issue we have had the opportunity to see Daredevil and the legendary (and original) Heroes for Hire, and the next will include a story where this unlikely pair will team up with Daredevil to help Sheldon Shipman and his sister.

Then back to harsh reality, a reality where Elektra has become the new "lethal weapon" Kingpin, organized crime lord of New York. But more interesting is that all this will tell us Ben Urich.

And attention because the new situation "contractual" Elektra cause a new and brutal confrontation between Daredevil and this dangerous killer.

In its final pages, the next issue will show a long-awaited moment: the return of the villain in the history of the Man Without Fear ...
name: Cazadores

description:
The cascading events unfold without possible interruption. Bullseye will mark the return of one of the most tragic and important in the history of Daredevil, a moment that will mean a before and after in the life of our hero scarlet. A new confrontation antre Bullseye and The Man Without Fear could be definitive.

Moreover, in the next issue will be on the return of one of the most important anti-heroes of the Marvel Universe history: Punisher, the hero / villain who once was confronted several times Spiderman.

And in the midst of so much tragedy and so many violent and dangerous characters, Matt Murdock decided that now is the time to change status. Who says there is time for everything in the life of a hero?
name: Condenados

description:
What do you get when you mix two down-and-out space-idiots, an angry space-sexpot, a priceless space-idol, and a herd of murderous, revenge-seeking space-zealots? How would we know--we asked you! See Quinn and Krunk try to entertain the trigger-happy 3-Dog and his faithful cohorts with their butt-clenching tale of high adventure. See Quinn finally sort out his relationship with the irresistible Neoki with the simple aid of a breaching bomb. See Krunk tackle the awesome task of figuring out what his mom wants for Mother's Day (what do you get a lady who wears a welding mask to the hair salon?), but figures out how to cure his insomnia--with a brick!

Created without a lick of shame by Zach Howard (Shaun of the Dead) and Sean Murphy (Scarecrow: Year One; Off Road), with screenwriter Reed Buccholz, Outer Orbit is high-velocity, intergalactic action that puts the ass in assinine, featuring more grown men in thongs than a Lance Bass calendar shoot!

Let's add up just exactly how stupid our intergalactic super zeros are, shall we? Did they blab to a poker-playing group of gangsters about the existence of a priceless idol? Check. And where to find it? Check. And that the key to open its lock box is around Krunk's neck? Check and mate. Suffice it to say, the crooks decide to go all-in and take Krunk's key and snatch the idol from the ultra-hot, and ultra-hot-tempered, Neoki, who's waiting for a mystery buyer to pony up hella cash for the treasured artifact. Of course, big bad Krunk isn't about to give up the key without a lot of collateral damage, and the boys manage to escape the mayhem and head toward the rendezvous with Neoki. With the gangsters in hot pursuit. And with the bounty-hunting Seekers in even hotter pursuit. Maybe all these thugs wouldn't be so eager to catch up if they knew Quinn still has a ticking time-bomb around his neck!

In the next issue a new "encounter" between Daredevil and Punisher. A story of great impact, where Frank Miller will emphasize the great differences regarding the ethics of each of these two characters. It is true that both are vigilant (moving through the streets and rooftops of New York), but so is everyone sees life (and pun intended) in a totally different.

And if recently the Man Without Fear was deprived of its most important power, the direction of the radar, now faces a very different situation ...

All that and the reappearance of one of the most characteristic of Daredevil villains. We refer to Zancudo. But maybe we should rectify and clarify that we will find more than one ...
name: ¡Está viva!

description: Goblins chew, goblins fight! Goblins cut, goblins bite! The goblins of Varisia sing twisted songs as their blood boils with ferocious rage and mystic power. Valeros and his companions may discover the forces behind the goblin tribes' newfound strength, but stopping it is another matter entirely. Paizo's incredible award-winning fantasy world, fiction line and tabletop RPG is now the ultimate fantasy comic from Dynamite Entertainment.
name: Dark Waters Rising Chapter 2

description:
Valeros and his companions have captured one of the cultists behind the strange magic that grips the goblin tribes of Varisia, but their prisoner may not be as helpless as they seem. Making matters worse, the group must cross through the haunted cemetery known as Pauper's Grave, luring them into the paralyzing touch of flesh-eating ghouls.

Paizo's incredible award-winning fantasy world, fiction line and tabletop RPG is now the ultimate fantasy comic from Dynamite Entertainment. Includes over 5 pages of character profiles and Pathfinder RPG game statistics, plus an EXCLUSIVE removable, playable tactical map and poster.
name: Dark Waters Rising Chapter 3

description:
In the final pages of this issue we have had the opportunity to see a spectacular scene where some "human spider" facing (between scarlet shadows) to a group of ninjas of the Hand. This is not a dream. The Black Widow is back and, in fact, become one of the major players in the next issue.

But not the only. And while we discover the reason Kirigi's body has been stolen, we find that another female character is gaining relevance in the ongoing storyline. Another female who has not ceased to be "present" in recent times. Of course, this is Elektra ...

Along the way, Daredevil will witness an unexpected loss.
name: Acabado

description: With Metropolis in the grip of a heat wave, Clark must track down and apprehend a teleporting criminal. Meanwhilte, are Lex's memories starting to return?
name: Detective Part 2

description: The classic creator-owned series collected for the first time! Carson Deeds is an emotionally troubled teen with a loaded shotgun beneath his bed and a list of classmates in his aim. When a suit of alien armor falls into Carson's hands, he stumbles across the power to live out every revenge fantasy he's ever dreamed. Or did the armor find him? Completely re-mastered with all-new story, art, and amazing color by Cirque Studios! Plus, a new cover by Andy Smith, with a back cover by Bart Sears.
name: TPB

description: Sally and Bernie Montgomery have found some disturbing information about the death of their baby daughter - but is it really an answer, or just another question? Malone, meanwhile, continues to search for Lucy Corliss' missing son Randy, but his investigation is soon to surprise him. Meanwhile, who really runs the CHiLDhood network, and who or what is GT-21...?

The multiple Hugo Award-winning steampunk webcomic, collected in hardcover! The Industrial Revolution has become all-out war! For centuries, the Heterodyne family of inventors kept the peace, but the last Heterodyne disappeared twenty years ago. At Transylvania Polygnostic University, Agatha Clay dreams of being a scientist herself, but her trouble concentrating dooms her to be a lowly minion at best. Swept up to Baron Klaus' Airship City, Agatha finds herself in the midst of the greatest minds of her generation - and she may hold the key to the control of the continent!
name: Agatha Awakens

description: Lost in time again, Ash confronts a dark menace in the Land of the Rising Sun. What will the Chosen One do when confronted by a force that creates an army of undead ninjas? It's undead mayhem and hi-jinx in Japan as the adventures of everyone's favorite chainsaw wielding hero continue!

Throughout the years the 10th Muse has teamed up with some of the top comics such as Shi, Savage Dragon, Tellos, Legend of Isis, and Judo Girl. All these amazing stories brought to you by top comic talent as Billy Tucci, Erik Larsen, Marv Wolfman, Roger Cruz and Mike Wieringo are put together in this single graphic novel. Also included is a never-before-seen crossover with Indie favourite Koni Wave!
name: Volume 4

description: The Doktor is back in ? print that is. The sold-out Doktor Sleepless #1 is now available as part of this special Manual #1. Here is the perfect way to check out the new on-going Ellis epic that has everyone talking, and now it is ads-free, full of extra material, and still the original cover price! As well as the full #1, the Doktor Sleepless Manual comes with ten full pages of back matter, including extended information (and perhaps a few clues…) on the technology and locales of Heavenside written by Warren Ellis for the doktorsleepless.com datashadow, and several all-new full-page paintings from maestro Felipe Massafera! This ideal entry point is available with a Regular cover by Jacen Burrows, a Painted Wraparound cover by Massafera, and a limited 1-in-15 Warning Sign.
Jokers not available in Alaska or Hawaii

What seemed impossible might happen ... The group of ninjas known by the name of the hand has managed to dig Elektra's body in order to bring her back. Will they succeed? And if so: is it the same as always?

All this and much more ... in the next issue, which will include the last comic of the first stage of Frank Miller in the collection. A truly chilling story where Man Without Fear live a "confrontation" of the most curious and singular with Bullseye. A fitting climax to a historic step.

Just then, Klaus Janson will become collectible absolute cartoonist. If already in the last issues of his contribution collectible. If already in his recent issues on the artistic contribution has been much more important than a single ink, its greater involvement ensures consistency graph of the new era of Daredevil.

description:
If we see Daredevil normally through the streets of New York, in the final pages of this issue appears in an "ecosystem" radically different: nothing less than an ocean liner. This is a story autoconclusiva (where nothing is what it seems) whose conclusion we shall see in the next issue.

Then a totally different story, where Matt Murdock will be hired by the best counterfeiter in the world. The situation is complicated by the Kingpin input stage.

But the most important moment of the next issue will mark the appearance of Wolverine. One of the most charismatic and popular mutants in the Marvel Universe form a sort of team-up with Daredevil to find ... Bullseye.But if the last time he was seen was bedridden and totally broken! Something important is happening ...
name: Resurreccion

description:
In the next issue occur all.New characters!A great storyline "The return of a mythical villain! And a new artist!

Matt Murdock undertake Japan travel to far to find one of his worst enemies: Bullseye. But once in the country of the Rising Sun, the search is not as simple as it might seem at first glance. In fact, New York's attorney will meet with a number of hazards that complicate their mission to end really unusual.

But what about Bullseye? Really has recovered from his wounds? Well ... the answer is positive inexorably.

This whole story cycle will be performed by the new artist of the series. Your name: William Johnson.
name: La sentencia

description:
Bullseye is back! It has done so triumphantly in a particularly good: Kingpin's office. Will we finally witness the new and highly anticipated showdown between Daredevil and Bullseye? We will not know until the end of our last story ... in the next issue.

Then Daredevil must save (again) the life of his partner Foggy Nelson. The current problem is that his right arm injury left him so stunned that need help to get the good life Foggy continue. Who can help? Maybe a spider superhero?

And if all that were not enough, in the next issue begins a grand cycle rife with shocking plot.

Everything begins when you make your appearance Micah Synn, the savage chief Kingorge.

description:
The next issue will debut a new villain who bring their own grain of sand to the cycle plot. Crossbow is a dangerous vigilante uses authentic tipped arrows "classic" (nothing to do with Hawkeye).

Just then, the "guest" was missing for the "party" so special is coming. We refer to the almost omnipotent Kingpin, the big boss of the Mafia in New York ... who, however, are beginning to see their power threatened by Micah Synn, the savage chief Kingorge, and does not like anything ...

But the news of No. 15 will not end here. There will be major changes in the creative team, and we must mention the addition of David Mazzucchelli on Daredevil illustrator post. An artist will mark a before and after in the collection.

description:
Started stage drawn by the legendary David Mazzucchelli, who in the next issue, in addition to the graphical part of the adventures of the Man Without Fear, assume responsibility for the argument of one of the stories.

And this will not be the only new creative team level, as the No. 16 will also include two numbers USA with story and screenplay by Harlan Ellison and Arthur Byron Cover, two of the authors of science fiction's most important American landscape.

In terms of plot is important to note that the confrontation between Micah and Kingpin will worsen even more, as the first hit to the second where else can hurt: their business. And if that strong enough, there will also be returning Ballesta, a return to Daredevil suffer in their own flesh ...
name: Ultimatum

description:
Micah Synn has tried to boycott businesses Kingpin. But his plan has not had the expected success and once again, the king of organized crime in New York has failed to protect their interests (even if this had to take personal charge of everything).

But in the next issue Micah Synn returns to the fray with a new strategy. Your plan will target the very public image Kingpin, making a newspaper published a story which cast doubt on the personal life of the mobster.

This pamphlet will be the beginning of a chain of events that will lead to one of the most important and far-reaching of this line of argument. The confrontation between the two "heads" will result in an unprecedented and unexpected: Daredevil will partner with Kingpin.
name: Supervivencia

description:
Undoubtedly Micah Synn saga has become one of the major storylines of the collection, both for the importance of events that has included as its own extension (a year of the original collection). The final conclusion will be seen in the first few pages of the next issue, and needless to say it will be a great final impact will not disappoint anyone ...

Daredevil then live a story set in the Western United States. A very special episode for two essential reasons: the graphic treatment of David Mazzucchelli and the "appearance" of the Two-Gun Kid himself.

Then the Man Without Fear will team up with the heroine to be his partner in the past. We refer, of course, the Black Widow.
name: Mentiras

description:
The next issue will be big news on a creative level. For starters ... a history of habitual writer, Denny O'Neil, drawn by Sal Buscema, with the expected return of the Joker, one of the major villains of the story of Daredevil.

And then ...A story written by Frank Miller! Yes sir, the author who became the man without fear in one of the most important characters in the Marvel Universe for the script returns a single episode that would be illustrated by the legendary John Buscema.Two true masters in one comic!

Also, at the end of the next number will David Mazzuchelli, graphics with full force, to draw a really creepy script O'Neil, whose development will take place in the streets and palaces of Venice. Daredevil changes the asphalt of New York by the water of the legendary Italian city.
name: Profecia

description:
The outcome of Daredevil trip to Venice we will see in the next issue. And then an episode in which the Man without Fear and Black Widow team up again.

But the highlight will be the Daredevil crossover with the mythical second part of the Secret Wars story in a truly unforgettable moments. The first one will show us how the legendary Almighty visit the offices of Nelson and Murdock to hire two lawyers to entrust an impossible job: legally seize the planet Earth!

With this premise, the writers Denny O'Neil and Jim Shooter develop an argument where Daredevil "see the light" and other things ...

In the last pages of this number, the man without fear will face a former opponent of Iron Man
name: Ciudad fantasma

description:
The next issue of the collectible comic books include three complete. The first revolves around a villain known for Spiderman fans. We refer to Vulture, one of the most sinister characters in the Marvel Universe.

In the second. Daredevil will face Gladiator, has redesigned its suit to have the aesthetics of a true gladiator in the glorious days of Rome, so that has changed the circular saw blade.

The third is a major event, because this is the first chapter of "Born Again", the mythical story-cycle by Frank Miller and David Mazzucchelli-considered one of the best Daredevil stories of all time. A graphic account essential to understand the essence of vigilante scarlet.
name: El precio

description:
The expected return of Frank Miller. First as co-writer of the story where the Gladiator reappears. And then Miller and Mazzucchelli become absolute authors to narrate "Born Again", one of the most important stories in the history of Daredevil, which begins with an unexpected event: Karen Page reveals the secret identity of Daredevil.

With this premise starts a cycle whose central argument we see (and read) in the next issue of the Collector. In its pages contemplate how Matt Murdock's life becomes a living hell (pun intended).

The most popular lawyer Marvel Universe suffer a merciless harassment and his whole life will collapse within hours to an extent hard to beat. And to accentuate the situation, the action will occur in the middle of Christmas season ...
name: Apocalipsis

description:
Matt Murdock's life has hit bottom. From being a lawyer famous social success, our hero has finally become a pariah ... almost no hope of salvation.

But in the final pages of this issue resurfaces the indomitable spirit of Matt Murdock, and in the next volume will see how the situation gets traced. However, the road will be fraught with problems. The most important of all will Nuke, a kind of super-soldier (brutal and crazed) rather seems the dark side of Captain America.

In the final apotheosis of "Born Again" will see precisely the Sentinel of Liberty himself and several of the Avengers, which will have a decisive influence on the conclusion of a story cycle that marks a before and after in the life of Matt Murdock. Daredevil will never again be the same.
name: Purgatorio

description:
In the next issue important and interesting surprises.

The number 236 USA, which appeared to mark the 25th Anniversary of Marvel Comics (1986). An episode written by Ann Nocenti-famous for its later stage in the collection of Daredevil, and illustrated by Barry Windsor-Smith, who already drew the character in his early days as a pro in the world of comics.

Two alternative accounts of Frank Miller: "What if Matt Murdock had become an agent of SHIELD?" and "What if Elektra had lived?" (which originates from the events in issue 8 of this collectible).

And two short stories in black and white, also by Frank Miller, appeared in Bizarre Adventures, in which Elektra again be the main character.
name: Armageddon

description:
The next issue will be the last of Collectible Daredevil and have a really special content signed by the author that deeply marked the fate of our hero along his unforgettable story contained in these pages. We refer, of course, Frank Miller.

Despite his long career in the own collection of Man Without Fear, topped in recent numbers to the mythical "Born Again", the first contact with Frank Miller Daredevil took place over four issues where Spiderman and our hero formed a very unique team-up.

Comics Forum now offers round off this cycle of argument in its entirety. A historic moment as curious as anyone should miss.
name: Soñador americano

description:
The Daredevil Collectible ends. Where numbers have been 25 Comics Forum has reissued some of the most important times and bright path of Man Without Fear.

The Collectable began with the mythical and extensive stage where Frank Miller Daredevil became one of the key characters in the Marvel Universe. Then came the stage of Klaus Janson, Denny O'Neil and David Mazzucchelli, ending in "Born Again", the great epic tandem Miller / Mazzuchelli.

Recent issues have included stories and alternative history where Frank Miller first drew Daredevil.

In short, a work indispensable to know the most representative of one of the greatest heroes of the House of Ideas.

The first collection of the new, acclaimed SWAMP THING series from the superstar team of writer SCOTT SNYDER and artist YANICK PAQUETTE! Alec Holland thought he knew the history of the Swamp Thing – but he was wrong! The war between The Green and The Red has begun, and the knights of decay walk the Earth unchecked! Collecting SWAMP THING #1-7!

Back Blurb

SWAMP THING REBORN!

Doctor Alec Holland used to be dead. A lab accident killed this brilliant botanist and biochemist, but he was resurrected as the shambling supernatural creature called Swamp Thing. Or so everyone thought.

The immortal spirits who guide the Green --- the vibrant force uniting all plant life --- used Holland's humanity as the seed for Swamp Thing, their greatest protector, but the real man himself remained dead in the ground...until sex weeks ago, when Holland awoke, alive, but cursed with the memories of the monster in his image.

Now Holland wants to put his past --- the Swamp Thing's past --- behind him. But the Green is not through with him yet. Its hours of darkness is upon it, as a new force threatens to rot away all life on earth.

The Green needs Doctor Alec Holland to become Swamp Thing again, for real this time. But this Swamp Thing will be no protector. This Swamp Thing will be a conquer...

Superstar writer SCOTT SNYDER (BATMAN, AMERICAN VAMPIRE) and acclaimed artist YANICK PAQUETTE (BATMAN INCORPORATED) and MARCO RUDY resurrect one of the most influential comic series of all time in SWAMP THING: RAISE THEM BONES --- a harrowing tale of heroism, horror, and the fertile ground in between.
name: Swamp Thing Volume 1 Raise Them Bones

Victor Frankenstein, a Swiss scientist, has a great ambition; to create intelligent life. But when his creature first stirs, he realizes he has constructed a monster. Abandoned by its maker and shunned by everyone else who sees it, the monster turns on its creator and haunts Dr. Frankenstein with murder and horrors to the very ends of the Earth. Artist Frazer Irving's cinematic and moving portrayal of the doctor and his creation is sympathetic and powerful.

This is a beautiful black and white graphic novel adaptation of Mary Shelley's classic novel.
